# Product Development Rules

## Architecture patterns in use

- Server actions for all mutations (no separate REST endpoints unless webhook/external)
- Supabase RLS for all data access — never bypass with service role key in client code
- shadcn/ui components — check components/ui/ before building new UI primitives
- Tailwind CSS 4 — no inline styles, no external CSS files

## The activation funnel is sacred

Any feature that touches: till sessions, sale recording, Z-report, or subscription must:

1. Preserve the existing recordGrowthMilestone calls
2. Add the corresponding Loops trackLoopsEvent call (see lib/loops.ts)
3. Not block the main user action with async email/analytics calls

## POS-specific rules

- POS sessions live in app/app/pos/ — changes here affect live till sessions
- Never break the completeSaleReturn flow — it is the primary revenue-generating action
- Kitchen display (KDS) and POS must stay in sync — test both when touching kitchenops.ts

## Stripe rules

- Webhook handler is at app/api/billing/webhook/route.ts
- Always verify webhook signature before processing
- Subscription status changes must update Supabase subscriptions table

## When adding a new page or route

- Check app/ structure before creating — follow existing folder conventions
- Add to sitemap if it's a marketing/public page
- Add to llms.txt if it's relevant for AI discoverability
